selectedType.title: Analysis report of the Baby Doge Coin
selectedType.detail: Baby Doge Coin is a meme cryptocurrency designed to be deflationary and more scarce over time. Holders earn more tokens automatically through a 5% fee from every on-chain transaction within the Baby Doge ecosystem. The token is available on multiple blockchain networks, including BNB Smart Chain, Ethereum, and Solana.

contractSecurity.title: Contract Source Code Verified
contractSecurity.description: This token contract is open source. You can check the contract code for details. Unsourced token contracts are likely to have malicious functions to defraud their users of their assets

contractSecurity.title: No Proxy
contractSecurity.description: There is no proxy in the contract. The proxy contract means contract owner can modifiy the function of the token and possibly effect the price.

contractSecurity.title: No Mint Function
contractSecurity.description: Mint function is transparent or non-existent. Hidden mint functions may increase the amount of tokens in circulation and effect the price of the token.

contractSecurity.title: No Function Found That Retrieves Ownership
contractSecurity.description: If this function exists, it is possible for the project owner to regain ownership even after relinquishing it

contractSecurity.title: No Hidden Owner
contractSecurity.description: No hidden owner address was found for the token. For contract with a hidden owner, developer can still manipulate the contract even if the ownership has been abandoned.

contractSecurity.title: This Token Can Not Self Destruct
contractSecurity.description: No self-destruct function found. If this function exists and is triggered, the contract will be destroyed, all functions will be unavailable, and all related assets will be erased.

contractSecurity.title: No External Call Risk found
contractSecurity.description: External calls would cause this token contract to be highly dependent on other contracts, which may be a potential risk.

honeypotRisk.description: Above 10% may be considered a high tax rate. More than 50% tax rate means may not be tradable.

list.title: This Does Not Appear To Be A Honeypot
list.description: We are not aware of any malicious code.

list.title: NO Codes Found To Suspend Trading
list.description: If a suspendable code is included, the token maybe neither be bought nor sold (honeypot risk).

list.title: No Trading Cooldown Function
list.description: The token contract has no trading cooldown function. If there is a trading cooldown function, the user will not be able to sell the token within a certain time or block after buying.

list.title: Anti-Whale Mechanism Exists (Limited Number Of Transactions)
list.description: There is a limit to the number of token transactions. The number of scam token transactions may be limited (honeypot risk).

list.title: Anti Whale Can  Be Modified
list.description: The maximum trading amount or maximum position can  be modified.

list.title: NO Blacklist
list.description: The blacklist function is not included. If there is a blacklist, some addresses may not be able to trade normally (honeypot risk).

list.title: Whitelist Function
list.description: Having a whitelist function means that, for this contract, some privileged users may have greater advantages in transactions, such as bypassing transaction limits, being exempt from taxes, trading earlier than others, or not being affected by transaction cooldown restrictions.

list.title: Tax Cannot Be Modified
list.description: The contract owner may not contain the authority to modify the transaction tax. If the transaction tax is increased to more than 49%, the tokens will not be able to be traded (honeypot risk).

list.title: No Tax Changes For Personal Addresses
list.description: No tax changes were found for every assigned address.If it exists, the contract owner may set a very outrageous tax rate for assigned address to block it from trading.
